# WiX v6 Installer Rules (FK Standard)

## Toolchain

| Tool | Version | Install |
|---|---|---|
| WiX CLI | 6.x | `dotnet tool install --global wix` |
| WixToolset.Sdk | 6.x | NuGet (SDK-style `.wixproj`) |
| WixToolset.UI.wixext | 6.x | PackageReference in `.wixproj` |
| WixToolset.Util.wixext | 6.x | PackageReference in `.wixproj` |

## Install Path

All FK desktop apps install to `C:\opt\DedgeWinApps\<AppName>\` — this is AppLocker-approved.

**Use `SetProperty` to override `INSTALLFOLDER` at runtime** (WiX auto-GUID generation requires a `StandardDirectory` parent in the source, but the actual path is injected via property):

```xml
<StandardDirectory Id="ProgramFiles64Folder">
  <Directory Id="INSTALLFOLDER" Name="AppName" />
</StandardDirectory>

<SetProperty Id="INSTALLFOLDER"
             Value="[%OptPath]\DedgeWinApps\AppName\"
             Before="AppSearch"
             Sequence="both" />
```

**Never** hardcode `C:\opt` — use `[%OptPath]` which is the `OptPath` environment variable.

Do NOT install to `C:\Program Files\` — AppLocker blocks execution from non-approved paths on FK servers.

## File Inclusion

**Do NOT use `HarvestDirectory` in `.wixproj`** — it is silently ignored in WiX SDK 6.0.2 and produces empty MSIs.

**Use `<Files>` glob in a dedicated `.wxs` file:**

```xml
<ComponentGroup Id="AppFiles" Directory="INSTALLFOLDER">
  <Files Include="..\AppProject\bin\Release\net10.0-windows\win-x64\publish\**\*" />
</ComponentGroup>
```

The app **must be published** before the installer is built:

```powershell
dotnet publish -c Release -r win-x64 --self-contained true
```

**Always use `--self-contained true`** — framework-dependent publish produces only 4–5 files and the app won't run on machines without the exact runtime version.

## NuGet Configuration

The installer project needs a local `NuGet.config` that includes both feeds:

```xml
<configuration>
  <packageSources>
    <add key="nuget.org" value="https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json" protocolVersion="3" />
    <add key="Dedge" value="https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/Dedge/Dedge/_packaging/Dedge/nuget/v3/index.json" />
  </packageSources>
</configuration>
```

## Platform

Always set `Platform` in the `.wixproj` `PropertyGroup`, not on individual components:

```xml
<PropertyGroup>
  <Platform>x64</Platform>
  <SuppressIces>ICE61;ICE80</SuppressIces>
</PropertyGroup>
```

## Custom Dialog Insertion

To insert a custom dialog into `WixUI_InstallDir`, use a **separate `<UI>` block with `Order="2"`**.

Do NOT use child elements inside `<ui:WixUI>` — WiX v6 does not support it (schema error).
Do NOT try to override built-in dialogs with `override="yes"` — WiX v6 Dialog does not support it.

```xml
<ui:WixUI Id="WixUI_InstallDir" InstallDirectory="INSTALLFOLDER" />

<UI>
  <DialogRef Id="MyCustomDlg" />
  <Publish Dialog="WelcomeDlg" Control="Next" Event="NewDialog" Value="MyCustomDlg" Order="2" Condition="1" />
  <Publish Dialog="MyCustomDlg" Control="Back" Event="NewDialog" Value="WelcomeDlg" Condition="1" />
  <Publish Dialog="MyCustomDlg" Control="Next" Event="NewDialog" Value="InstallDirDlg" Condition="1" />
</UI>
```

When adding a licence agreement, insert the custom dialog after `LicenseAgreementDlg` instead:

```xml
<Publish Dialog="LicenseAgreementDlg" Control="Next" Event="NewDialog" Value="MyCustomDlg" Order="2"
         Condition="LicenseAccepted = &quot;1&quot;" />
```

## Custom Actions

- **PowerShell scripts** must use `pwsh.exe` (PowerShell 7), never `powershell.exe`
- **Deferred** actions run elevated; use `Impersonate="yes"` to run as the installing user
- **Pass properties to deferred actions** with `<SetProperty>` in the execute sequence
- **Keep command length under 255 chars** — extract logic to a `.ps1` file installed alongside the app
- **Launch after install** in `InstallUISequence` with `asyncNoWait` (fire and forget, user context):

```xml
<CustomAction Id="LaunchApp" Directory="INSTALLFOLDER" Execute="immediate"
              Return="asyncNoWait"
              ExeCommand="&quot;[INSTALLFOLDER]App.exe&quot;" />
<InstallUISequence>
  <Custom Action="LaunchApp" After="ExecuteAction" Condition="NOT Installed AND NOT REMOVE" />
</InstallUISequence>
```

## Kill Running Process on Upgrade

```xml
<util:CloseApplication Id="CloseExisting"
                       Target="App.exe"
                       CloseMessage="yes"
                       RebootPrompt="no"
                       TerminateProcess="0"
                       Timeout="5" />
```

`TerminateProcess` takes an **integer exit code**, not `"yes"`.

## Product Metadata

Add these properties for Add/Remove Programs info:

```xml
<Property Id="ARPCOMMENTS"      Value="Description of the app" />
<Property Id="ARPCONTACT"       Value="IT-support, Dedge AS" />
<Property Id="ARPHELPLINK"      Value="https://www.Dedge.no" />
<Property Id="ARPURLINFOABOUT"  Value="https://www.Dedge.no" />
<Property Id="ARPHELPTELEPHONE" Value="+47 22 31 50 00" />
```

## Licence Agreement

Add a Norwegian Dedge licence via an RTF file:

```xml
<WixVariable Id="WixUILicenseRtf" Value="License.rtf" />
```

The RTF must use ASCII encoding with Norwegian chars as RTF unicode escapes (e.g. `\u248\'f8` for ø).

## Branding Bitmaps

Two bitmaps are required. See `docs/WiX-Bitmap-Layout-Reference.md` for pixel-precise zone maps.

| Variable | Size | Content |
|---|---|---|
| `WixUIBannerBmp` | 493×58 px | White background. Small app icon (40×40) right-aligned at (445, 9). Left area reserved for WiX title text — do NOT paint there. |
| `WixUIDialogBmp` | 493×312 px | Left panel (0–163px): dark FK green with branding (icon, product name, version). Right panel (164–493px): plain white — WiX renders title/description here. |

### Critical: DrawIcon vs DrawImage

**Never use `DrawIcon()`** — it renders at the icon's native size (often 256×256).
**Always convert to bitmap and use `DrawImage()` with explicit width/height:**

```powershell
$ico = New-Object System.Drawing.Icon("app.ico", 48, 48)
$bmp = $ico.ToBitmap(); $ico.Dispose()
$g.DrawImage($bmp, x, y, 48, 48)  # Explicit size
```

### WiX text rendering behaviour

- Built-in WelcomeDlg text uses `Transparent="yes"` and renders directly on the bitmap
- Font color is **system default** — black on light-mode, potentially invisible on dark-mode
- You **cannot change** the font color of built-in dialog text in `WixUI_InstallDir`
- Safe strategy: paint branding in the left panel only, leave right panel white for WiX text

## Silent Install / Uninstall

```powershell
# Install (elevated, verbose log)
Start-Process msiexec -ArgumentList "/i `"Setup.msi`" /quiet /norestart /l*v `"C:\temp\install.log`" MYPROP=value" -Verb RunAs -Wait

# Uninstall
$prod = Get-ItemProperty "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Uninstall\*" |
        Where-Object { $_.DisplayName -like "*My App*" } | Select-Object -First 1
Start-Process msiexec -ArgumentList "/x $($prod.PSChildName) /quiet /norestart" -Verb RunAs -Wait
```

## GUIDs

Generate fresh GUIDs with `[System.Guid]::NewGuid()` in PowerShell.
**Never reuse GUIDs** from another installer — MSI uses them for component tracking.

## Things That Do NOT Work in WiX v6

| What | Why | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `HarvestDirectory` in `.wixproj` | Silently ignored in SDK 6.0.2 | `<Files Include="...\**\*" />` in `.wxs` |
| Child elements inside `<ui:WixUI>` | Schema error | Separate `<UI>` block |
| `Dialog override="yes"` | Not a valid attribute on Dialog | Cannot override built-in dialogs |
| `TerminateProcess="yes"` | Must be integer | Use `"0"` |
| `Directory Id="TARGETDIR"` | Conflicts with virtual symbol | Use `StandardDirectory` |
| `C:\Program Files\` install path | AppLocker blocked | `[%OptPath]\DedgeWinApps\` |
| `DrawIcon()` in bitmap generation | Renders at native icon size (256px) | `DrawImage()` with explicit w×h |
| Framework-dependent publish | Only 4 files, app won't run | `--self-contained true` |
